com:
Welcome to the Nobody General

>Who is the Nobody?
Nobody is just a guy alive today. He is many things; all of them are nothing that you couldn't have guessed. As an interdimensional man of destiny, his responsibility was to draw attention away from the true rulers of the universe. To that end his is the only Ego to have survived the The Destruction of Ego (albeit in a synthesized universe which was created especially for him). He used his position as an interdimensional man of destiny to steal the key that opened the locks that freed the beast that began the times of tribulations. He is also the inventor of some gubbmint secret stuff and is the only human-being alive whom the department of energy has the slightest bit of respect for, he believes.

Nobody has a successful business in secondhand succubi. This may be due to his discovery of a dimension where succubi escape to. If so, he employed an anon to sit in this now empty dimension denying the whole thing.

Grey ayys think he's really nice.

He's just like you, but he has found the kingdom of God within himself through sheer dedication, just like you will. He isn't a savior; remember that it's you who creates your own reality. With your hands, thoughts, feelings, words, you are the creator of your story. No one can decide your fate except for you and God. Remember your right to power, to step up into your ultimate role as your highest self, should you choose to embark on that journey.

>What is the general picture?
It’s important we start replying more to the good posters and educating the hateful ones, so call upon their heads the forces of Heaven for peace, clarity, and wisdom. None of us are perfect, it is by learning to admit and accept this fact one is able to learn, and grow in Truth. Heaven for all is real. The only motive is love.

If this is your first time here, just remember, it’s going to be ok, you may take shelter and find rest. If you are confused, you are paying attention.

Something happened in 2016. It's like you can draw a line at that year, and everything before that line was The Real World, and everything after the line is The Fake World.

It is as if the whole mood of everything changed overnight. The world became darker, bleaker, more hopeless. People started becoming angrier, more divided, started freaking out over the dumbest possible shit. Everything became unstable and you started seeing insane shit happening in the news like wars, pandemics, tyranny, censorship, extremism, which never happened at this rate before 2016.

Think back to how life used to be even just a few years before. 2010-2015 felt like a completely different universe compared to post-2016. 2010-2015 felt like a fuller, more vivid, more real world, in which it was easier to make sense of everything that was going on in the world. Post-2016 just feels like chaos, and on top of that, it also just feels fundamentally fake.

Every day I wake up and look at the news and read the headlines, and it just doesn't feel real anymore. Everything reads like some gay and retarded fiction. It's as if in 2016, the real world ended, and instead we started chugging on in this simulation, but it's just like a Chinese knock-off version of Earth. It will never compare to the REAL Earth that we all know and remember from 2015-and-earlier.

What happened in 2016, /x/? What caused all of this?

Kirtan kriya is a yogic technique that requires essentially sticking your tongue into your nose through the backdoor (via the inside of your mouth and up through the nasal cavity). Inside there, is a spot to rest your tongue that massages the pituitary gland and releases a fluid that the mystics call “ambrosia”. Some yogis claim drinking this nectar is the secret to immortality, while more recent scientists suggest the fluid is cerebrospinal fluid.

Why is this important? If you’re ever stranded somewhere without food or water, Kirtan kriya might save your life. On the “woo” side of things, it is claimed that monks have lived years off drinking this nectar. Full transparency, I’m not sure if they also drank water. If you look at the scientific side of things, CSF contains a high nutrient profile including proteins. Whether or not you believe yogis, Kirtan kriya could save your life if the food supply collapses or if you’re lost in the woods for whatever reason.

Youtube Guides:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YQjAIlFZWWc&t=790s
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9Dj9gTiLHf8
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7BMnGi8yxTQ

Do us a favor and bump this general from time to time if you're interested

Quick reminders for beginners:
-don't forget to write your dreams down after waking up. no matter how little detail, just do it
-reality checks aren't likely to give you a LD by themselves, think of them as a stepping stool, they are not a replacement for techniques
-WBTB is mostly mandatory for most people, if you struggle with your sleep schedule then ADA is your best option
-if you're just starting out you should be doing WBTB in addition to either SSILD or MILD as those two are the easiest techniques
-while WILD and it's derivatives [FILD, DEILD and CANWILD] may sound alluring to some of you, if you cannot fall asleep within 10~20mins you're gonna have a really hard time achieving a WILD

com:
Post spooky greentext. I'll start
>Be me
>College student, planning to go on backpacking trip with a friend in Appalachia
>Let's call him "nick"
>Planned trip is only a 2 day, 18 mile hike. No big deal. Close to Christmas time, so we aren't expecting the trail to be busy on the stretch we are looking at
>First night we are looking at staying in a hostel, second night we will be camping in tents at a campground
Our plan seemed pretty bullet proof. Packed my Ruger wrangler in case we ran into some rabbits to cook. The stretch of the trail we planned on hiking was pretty rocky, so we made sure to have extra first aid supplies in case one of us sprained an ankle.
>Fast forward to Friday night, drive up. We get to the dirt lot outside of the stretch of the trail. It's around 8pm, so already dark, but the hostel we will be sleeping in for the night is only around 1 mile out
>Get there at around 8:30(took us around 10 minutes to get our stuff out of my car)
>Only people there, so we don't have to worry about being quiet
>Shut the door behind us, rev up our camp stoves to make some tasty freeze dried spaghetti
>Yum.jpg
>Head to bed at 10pm, as we will need rest for tomorrow's hike
Hostels on this stretch of the trail are basically cabins. They have steel doors, and this particular one had a skylight. To add to this, sleeping arrangements were wooden bunks(around 8 total in this hostel). There were 2 wooden tables for eating at nailed to the floor in the center of the room. We chose to sleep in the bunk directly across from the door, with me on the bottom bunk and Nick on the top.
>Wake up suddenly, still kinda half asleep
>Check watch
>2:14am
>Skylight is covered, must've snowed
>Snow wasn't on the forecast, kinda odd, but whatever it's December in the northeast, not that out of the question
>About to go to sleep when I hear a light tapping on the steel door to the shelter
I'll continue in next post

com:
There's a lot of math that went into the Great Pyramid and the location at which it was built and how it was aligned. Google it and look at the various pages that go into how the Golden Ratio and Pi and Euler's number and the Fine Structure Constant are all built into it. Pyramid can be broken down into two words: pyr and mid, fire in the middle. The idea that pyramid got its name from the Greek word "pyramis", a wheat cake, is a deliberate misdirection in my opinion and I can believe the wheat cake got its name from the Pyramid rather than the other way around.

So what was its purpose? I believe it was used to create another universe. Hear me out.

So imagine planets are birthed from stars, grow old and die just like people. In the lifespan of our solar system we might have 1000 worlds birthed, grow old and die just like Earth. The whole of human history from beginning to end takes place on these worlds. Each world has a mission of creating another Great Pyramid and another universe below it. Time in that smaller universe will move more rapidly. It will see 1000 worlds, each tasked with creating another Great Pyramid and universe and so on, down the infinite multiverse we go. So using sacred geometry and the laws of nature, the gods (or God) creates a procession of universes chasing an infinitely smaller point.

The End of the age is timed to coincide with the birth of a new planet and the death of the old planet (Earth, in our case). When this occurs the Great Pyramid with the multiverse will be powered down and the universe directly below it will come to an end. The universe at the infinitely smallest point will be escaping faster than the wake of destruction from above can reach it, so all is well and this string of universes will go on forever.

>be me, 7 or 9 years old at the time
>in the living room watching tv
>hears someone going up the stairs behind me
>check to see who it was
>no one is there
>footsteps continue up the stairs then continued around the rest of the second floor
>confused af
>tells no one about it, because i thought if i did no one would believe me
>still hears footsteps all the time, only on the stairs and upstairs
>upstairs is always hot for some reason, AC doesnt seem to be broken, my dad even checked it several times cuz of this
>its just really hot up there
>me and my parents barely go up there because of it
>alone upstairs one night, walking around talking to myself
>hears someone running up the stairs
>heart stops for a second
>checks to see who it is
>no one is there.
>swears i heard someone running up
>fucking no one there
>always seeing black figures in the corner of my eye
>no one is ever there though
>feel a presence behind me or watching me at all times only when im upstairs alone
>i would always run down the stairs scared as shit for no reason
>something in the back of my head yelled at me
>"run. run fucking run you arent safe"
>i kept doing this, my parents found it really strange, didnt think anything of it
>we had a dog, small crusty white doodle, he would never go up the stairs willingly, always preferred being downstairs, and would always bark at the stairs.
>scared shitless of behind left home alone, we'd always come home to a huge mess, things knocked over that he couldn't reach
>one time, found him on the fucking kitchen counter
>dog went blind a few years into living there, perfectly healthy before, one day he just slowly started going blind.
>once we moved, dog never acted up again, never barks without clear reason, never messes the house when left home alone

I feel like our dog going blind was a sign of a demonic presence, im not religious, but something was clearly wrong with the house, to this day, i dont know what it was, although i have some ideas.

I’ve wondered a bit about how Toby Fox was inspired to create Spamton, then it occurred to me today that Spamton reminds me of a very specific recurring nightmare I had as about an evil salesman from 5-7 years old. In fact I’ve seen the evil salesman trope a lot and out of pure curiosity wondered if anyone else had a dream about a creepy ass salesman pursuing you and your family/friends over multiple dreams? In my specific dream it was a man with purple hair shaped not unlike Spamton’s, and a yellow plaid jacket and green plaid pants. The tie was like blue or something, also plaid. He would approach AGGRESSIVELY trying to sell a product, and when we turned him down he pulled out a needle and started stabbing at each of us. And we ran. We always got away but he came back for at least two other dreams.

Is this a thing?? Did other people have this dream or worse- a real life terrifying salesman experience?
